Inner Shelf

Join the community that brings together self-help seekers and licensed therapists for guided book groups online. Read, reflect, and grow with like-minded individuals committed to life-changing transformation.


What Youll Get

  • Professionally Guided: Licensed therapists lead each virtual session to deepen your understanding and foster growth.
  • Affordable Growth: Experience personal transformation at a fraction of the cost of individual therapy.
  • Community Connection: Share perspectives and connect virtually with others who are equally committed to self-improvement.
  • Convenient Access: Join live, virtual (Zoom) sessions from the comfort of your own home, making it easy to fit personal growth into your busy schedule.


Who is Inner Shelf for?

Are you eager to grow? Do you thrive in a group setting, and value learning through shared and varied perspectives? Inner Shelf is perfect for anyone looking for the structure and accountability of a group, combined with the insights of a licensed therapist to guide your self-growth journey.

How it works

  1. Choose Your Book: Select from a range of self-help books tailored to various aspects of personal growth.
  2. Choose Your Therapist: Commit to a group program with one of our top-notch, licensed therapists. Youll meet online each week to discuss each chapter, guided by a licensed therapist.
  3. Prepare with Ease: Too busy to read the chapters for your upcoming group meeting? We provide chapter summaries and reflection prompts in advance of each session to help you quickly catch up.
  4. Grow Together: Reflect, share, and learn alongside a supportive community as you work toward life-changing transformation.

Frequently Asked Questions


Q: What books are available to choose from?

A: Our curated list includes popular self-help and personal growth titles selected for their transformational potential.


Q: How long does each program last?

A: Programs typically run for 4 weeks, meeting once a week.


Q: Do I need to buy the book separately?

A: Yes, participants are responsible for obtaining their own copy of the book. We provide purchase links to Amazon, Barnes & Noble, and GoodReads for your convenience.
